ジタル=\"デジタル\" 教科書体=\"教科書体\" np-r\",serif;\"=\"np-r',serif;'\" style=\"font-size:13.28px;caret-color:rgb(34,34,34);color:rgb(34,34,34);font-family:;\">》</span></div>", "Review Previous Material"], "授業外学習2": "As a general rule, students should expect to spend one to two minutes of study outside of class for every minute of class time."}, "評価": {"教科書/Required texts0": ["Kenneth B. Pyle, \"The Japanese Question,\" (AEI Press, 1996), ISBN: 0-8447-3799-2.\nTanaka Akihiko, \"Japan in Asia: Post-Cold-War Diplomacy, (Japan Publishing Industry Foundation for Culture, 2017), ISBN: 978-4-916055-63-7."], "教科書/Required texts1": ["Kenneth B. Pyle", "The Japanese Question", "AEI Press", "1996 年", "0-8447-3799-2", ""], "教科書/Required texts2": ["Tanaka Akihiko", "Japan in Asia: Post Cold-War Diplomacy", "Japan Publishing Industry Foundation for Culture", "2017 年", "978-4-916055-63-7", ""], "参考書/Reference books0": ["著者名\nAuthor", "タイトル\nTitle", "発行所\nPublisher", "出版年\nYear of Publication", "ISBN", "ボタン\nButton"], "参考書/Reference books1": ["ケネス B. パイル", "日本への疑問", "サイムル出版社", "1995 年", "978-4377310528", ""], "参考書/Reference books2": ["田中明彦", "アジアの中の日本", "NTT出版", "2007 年", "978-4757140936", ""], "参考文献・資料/Reference books0": ["ケネス B. パイル, 『日本への疑問』, (サイムル出版社, 1995), ISBN: 978-4377310528.\n田中明彦, 『アジアの中の日本』(NTT出版, 2007), ISBN: 978-4757140936."], "学位授与の方針との関連Relationship to Diploma Policy0": ["This course will help students to understand and analyze problems in international relations, particularly those that deal with those of people from different regions and cultures. In addition, it will help them to develop their powers of autonomous learning by giving them the skills to identify the sorts of problems that require investigation.\n\n各授業科目は、各学部・研究科の定めるディプロマ・ポリシー（DP）・カリキュラム・ポリシー（CP）に基づき、カリキュラム上に配置されています。\nDP・CPを意識して本授業科目の学修を進めることで、各学部・研究科の期待する能力が養成されます。\n各学部・研究科のDP、CPや教育課程表（授業科目一覧等）は、下記リンクこちらに掲載していますので学修計画の参考にしてください。\nhttps://kwic.kwansei.ac.jp/cabinet/reference?typeCd=0&amp;cabinetId=557&amp;directLink=1\n※kwicへのリンクとなります（在学生のみ閲覧可）"], "成績評価Grading0": ["種別　Type備考　Note", "割合　Percentage", "評価基準等　Grading Criteria etc."], "成績評価Grading1": ["授業中試験／In-class examination (03)", "40 %", ""], "成績評価Grading2": ["その他／Others (99)", "60 %", "First In-Class Test, Participation"], "成績評価Grading3": ["備考　Note Students will be expected to participate in class discussions and may be asked to complete small assignments from time to time. These will factor into the participation grade which is twenty-five percent of the final grade. There will be an in-class midterm test and an in-class exam. These will be worth 35% and 40% of the grade respectively."], "更新日時/Date of Update0": ["2026年02月12日 18時48分53秒"], "項番No.0": [], "項番No.1": ["2026年度", "秋学期／Fall", "火曜４時限／Tuesday 4", "秋学期／Fall", "Ｇ－ＩＳ１０４"]}, "campas": 0, "name": "【320】Japan's Foreign Relations／Japan's Foreign Relations [EN]", "管理部署": 10, "単位数": 2, "担当者": "ウォルシュ　Ｂ．（WALSH BRIAN） ", "履修基準年度": "１年", "履修登録方法": "申込制(他条件あり)", "開講期": 2, "時限1": 10, "時限1_term": 1, "評価1": 2, "評価2": 6, "成績評価備考": "備考　Note\nStudents will be expected to participate in class discussions and may be asked to complete small assignments from time to time. These will factor into the participation grade which is twenty-five percent of the final grade. There will be an in-class midterm test and an in-class exam. These will be worth 35% and 40% of the grade respectively."}